data.name: Vegetarian Burrito
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty and flavorful vegetarian burrito packed with fresh ingredients and spices.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add diced onion and bell pepper, saut√© until softened (about 5 minutes).
Stir in black beans, corn, taco seasoning, and lime juice. Cook for another 5 minutes until heated through.
Warm tortillas in a separate pan or microwave until pliable.
Assemble burritos: place a scoop of the bean mixture on each tortilla, add sliced avocado, shredded cheese, and a dollop of sour cream. Sprinkle with chopped cilantro.
Roll the tortillas tightly and serve with additional lime wedges.
data.detailedName: Vegetarian Burrito with Black Beans and Avocado
data.modifiersForBase: Vegetarian filling with fresh vegetables and beans
